result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

01:04 PM Cases 15CF197, 16CF61, 17CF262, 17CF289, 17CF290, 17CF291, 17CM313, 18CF03, 18CF101, 18CF153 called together.  Defendant, Janine Jacalyn Cowle, appeared with Attorney Bruce Patrick Anderson.  Attorney Joseph M. Schieffer appeared for the State.  Cases are on for a plea hearing.  Case is on for Plea/Sentencing Hearing.  Agreement is recited by Attorney Anderson: Def to plead G to Count 1 in 15CF197 with a joint recommendation of 6 months minimum jail sentence imposed and guidelines fine for OWI 4th, AODA, 3 year revocation, 3 year IID; Count 2 DRI, Count 3 Merged.  In 18CF03: G to Counts 1 and 2: Felony bail jump.  Plead NC to Counts 1 and 5 in 18CF153.  DRI other cases/charges.  Withheld sentence on everything she pleads to with 3 years probation: required to complete Victim Impact Panel, 1 year conditional jail time concurrent: conditions of probation: maintain absolute sobriety, gainful employment, no entry in establishments whose primary purpose is the sale/distribution of alcohol, no contact with WS, pay applicable court costs, eligible for good time on 6 months on the OWI, but not on year of conditional jail time for other charges.  Atty Anderson requests def be eligible for work release if the program becomes available; State does not object to electronic monitoring.  Jail credit= 131 days as it relates to the OWI, stipulated to.  174 days served total for all cases.  Signed PLQ submitted to court.  Court asks def if they understand the agreement.  Def does.  Court reviews Defs constitutional rights.  Def understands what def is waiving those rights by entering into agreement today.  Court asks Def if they understand Court is not bound by agreement, and could order maximum penalties.  Def understands.  Court asks for pleas.  
In 15CF197 Count 1: OWI (4th) def enters G plea.
In 18CF03 Count 1: Bail jumping (F) def enters G plea; Count 2: Bail jumping (F) def enters G plea.
Defendant pleads No Contest in 18CF153 to Count 1: Battery (domestic abuse enhancer) (M) and No Contest to Count 5: Throw/discharge bodily fluid at public safety worker or prosecutor. 
Court finds a factual basis to accept the pleas.  Court finds def is making pleas knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily.  Court finds defendant guilty of noted counts and orders a JOC; remaining cases and counts are DRI for purposes of sentencing and restitution.  Case is Victim's Rights compliant.  DA asks Court to accept agreement.  Defense attorney asks Court to accept agreement; requests deferred reporting date for conditional jail time.  Def does not make statement to the Court.  
Court orders: 
15CF197 Count 1: OWI (4th) (F): 3 years probation, 6 months conditional jail time; good time eligible: 135 to serve, 131 days jail credit, 4 days left to serve, withheld sentence, (based upon completion of treament- reduces BAC) assesses $2552.00 in fines/costs, OWI Assessment and driver safety plan, revoke DL for 3 years, IID on any vehicle def owns/intends to drive for 3 years.
18CF03 Count 1: Bail jumping (F): 3 years probation, 1 year conditional jail time, not good time eligible, 43 days jail credit for conditional jail time, withheld sentence. $518 in costs/fees; has 30 days to determine where she will report. 
              Count 2: Bail jumping (F): 3 years probation, withheld sentence, $518 in costs/fees
18CF153 Count 1: Battery (domestic abuse enhancer) (M): 1 year probation, no conditional jail, withheld sentence $443 costs/fees plus the $100 domestic abuse surcharge.
                 Count 5: Throw/discharge bodily fluid at public safety worker or prosecutor (F): 1 year probation, withheld sentence, $518 costs/fees

Conditions of probation: maintain absolute sobriety, maintain gainful employment, no entry to any establishment whose primary purposes of selling/serving alcohol- except for purposes of employment (at agent's discretion), no contact with Wallace Stay, pay all applicable costs and fees, engage in Victim Impact Panel within 1st year of probation, after bond, will owe $1,049.00 after bond has been applied to all cases- minimum monthly payments of $100; If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.  No use/possession of firearm for life.  No voting in any election until civil rights are restored.  Must report to jail within 30 days of today, must call and establish reporting date within 7 days, eligible to serve on electronic monitor, will be eligible for Huber if gainfully employed.  If she can pay the $72 upfront for electronic monitoring, may also serve the 4 days remaining on conditional jail time on electronic monitoring, starting today.  Inform Tessa Anderson if using electronic monitoring for 1 year conditional jail time at least 5 days in advance of reporting date.  
Appeal rights provided.  
DNA to be provided to the Sheriff before leaving the building.
